msgid ""
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "29. Sāsaṅkasikkhāpada"
msgstr "29. The training rule on what is risky"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-np.29.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.29.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.156"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2400"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū vutthavassā āraññakesu senāsanesu viharanti."
msgstr ""
"At that time monks who had completed the rains residence were staying in "
"wilderness dwellings."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid "Kattikacorakā bhikkhū—"
msgstr ""
"Thieves who were active during the month of Kattika attacked the monks, "
"thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "“laddhalābhā”ti paripātenti."
msgstr "“They have obtained things.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The monks told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid ""
"“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āraññakesu senāsanesu viharantena tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ "
"aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipitun”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow monks who are staying in wilderness dwellings to store one "
"of their three robes in an inhabited area.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.263"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.29.1.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2401"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū—“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ āraññakesu senāsanesu "
"viharantena tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipitun”ti "
"tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipitvā atirekachārattaṃ "
"vippavasanti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Master had made this allowance, monks stored one of their "
"three robes in inhabited areas, and they stayed apart from them for more "
"than six days."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "Tāni cīvarāni nassantipi vinassantipi ḍayhantipi undūrehipi khajjanti."
msgstr "The robes were lost, destroyed, burnt, and eaten by rats."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū duccoḷā honti lūkhacīvarā."
msgstr "As a consequence those monks became poorly dressed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Other monks asked them"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, āvuso, duccoḷā lūkhacīvarā”ti?"
msgstr "why,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told them what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare "
"nikkhipitvā atirekachārattaṃ vippavasissantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can those monks store one of their three robes in an inhabited area and "
"then stay apart from it for more than six days?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2402"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū te anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ "
"ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.157"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ "
"antaraghare nikkhipitvā atirekachārattaṃ vippavasantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks do this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ "
"antaraghare nikkhipitvā atirekachārattaṃ vippavasissanti."
msgstr ""
"Monks, how can those foolish men store one of their three robes in an "
"inhabited area and then stay apart from it for more than six days?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2403"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid ""
"“Upavassaṃ kho pana kattikapuṇṇamaṃ yāni kho pana tāni āraññakāni senāsanāni "
"sāsaṅkasammatāni sappaṭibhayāni tathārūpesu bhikkhu senāsanesu viharanto "
"ākaṅkhamāno tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipeyya, siyā "
"ca tassa bhikkhuno kocideva paccayo tena cīvarena vippavāsāya."
msgstr ""
"‘There are wilderness dwellings that are considered risky and dangerous. "
"After observing the Kattika full moon that ends the rainy season, a monk who "
"is staying in such a dwelling may store one of his three robes in an "
"inhabited area, if he so desires, so long as he has a reason for staying "
"apart from that robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid "Chārattaparamaṃ tena bhikkhunā tena cīvarena vippavasitabbaṃ."
msgstr "He should stay apart from that robe for six days at the most."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.19"
msgid ""
"Tato ce uttari vippavaseyya, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"If he stays apart from it beyond that, except if the monks have agreed, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs1.2.20"
msgid "(<em>29</em>:<strong>48</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.29.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2404"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Upavassaṃ kho panāti"
msgstr "After observing:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "vuṭṭhavassānaṃ."
msgstr "after completing the rainy season."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2405"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Kattikapuṇṇamanti"
msgstr "The Kattika full moon that ends the rainy season:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "kattikacātumāsinī vuccati."
msgstr ""
"the fourth full moon of the rainy season in the month of Kattika is what is "
"meant."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2406"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "Yāni kho pana tāni āraññakāni senāsanānīti"
msgstr "There are wilderness dwellings:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "āraññakaṃ nāma"
msgstr "it is called a wilderness dwelling"

#. The text reads “five hundred bow-lengths,” <i lang="pli">pañcadhanusatikaṃ</i>. According to <ref>Sp-ṭ.2.92</ref>: “A measure of nine hand-spans of an ordinary hand, or a measure of four fore-arms when the bowstring is attached, this is called the teacher’s bow length,” <i lang="pli">ācariyadhanu nāma pakatihatthena navavidatthippamāṇaṃ, jiyāya pana āropitāya catuhatthappamāṇa</i>. The teacher’s bow-length is the standard measure for bow-lengths, see <ref>Sp. 2.301.15</ref>. Given the estimate of 50 cm for one forearm (a <i lang="pli">hattha</i>, sometimes translated as “cubit”) in BMC I, pp. 565-566, five hundred bow-lengths add up to about one kilometer.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "senāsanaṃ pañcadhanusatikaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr "if it is at least one kilometer away from any inhabited area."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.158"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2407"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Sāsaṅkaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Risky:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.9"
msgid ""
"ārāme ārāmūpacāre corānaṃ niviṭṭhokāso dissati, bhuttokāso dissati, "
"ṭhitokāso dissati, nisinnokāso dissati, nipannokāso dissati."
msgstr ""
"in the monastery, or in the vicinity of the monastery, thieves have been "
"seen camping, eating, standing, seated, or lying down."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2408"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Sappaṭibhayaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Dangerous:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.11"
msgid ""
"ārāme ārāmūpacāre corehi manussā hatā dissanti, viluttā dissanti, ākoṭitā "
"dissanti."
msgstr ""
"in the monastery, or in the vicinity of the monastery, thieves have been "
"seen injuring, robbing, or beating people."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2409"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "Tathārūpesu bhikkhu senāsanesu viharantoti"
msgstr "A monk who is staying in such a dwelling:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "evarūpesu bhikkhu senāsanesu viharanto."
msgstr "a monk who is staying in that kind of dwelling."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.264"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2410"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Ākaṅkhamānoti"
msgstr "If he so desires:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "icchamāno."
msgstr "if he so wishes."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2411"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "Tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaranti"
msgstr "One of his three robes:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "saṅghāṭiṃ vā uttarāsaṅgaṃ vā antaravāsakaṃ vā."
msgstr "the outer robe, the upper robe, or the lower robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2412"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "Antaraghare nikkhipeyyāti"
msgstr "May store […] in an inhabited area:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "samantā gocaragāme nikkhipeyya."
msgstr "may store it anywhere in his alms village."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2413"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "Siyā ca tassa bhikkhuno kocideva paccayo tena cīvarena vippavāsāyāti"
msgstr "So long as he has a reason for staying apart from that robe:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "siyā paccayo siyā karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "if there is a reason, if there is something to be done."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2414"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "Chārattaparamaṃ tena bhikkhunā tena cīvarena vippavasitabbanti"
msgstr "He should stay apart from that robe for six days at the most:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "chārattaparamatā vippavasitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he should stay apart from it for six days at the maximum."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2415"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.24"
msgid "Aññatra bhikkhusammutiyāti"
msgstr "Except if the monks have agreed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.25"
msgid "ṭhapetvā bhikkhusammutiṃ."
msgstr "unless he has the permission of the monks."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2416"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.26"
msgid "Tato ce uttari vippavaseyyāti"
msgstr "If he stays apart from it beyond that:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.27"
msgid "sattame aruṇuggamane nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "the robe becomes subject to relinquishment at dawn on the seventh day."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.29"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.30"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
#. VAR: vippavutthaṃ → vippavuṭṭhaṃ (c1, c2)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.31"
msgid ""
"idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ atirekachārattaṃ vippavutthaṃ, aññatra "
"bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this robe which I have stayed apart from for more than six days "
"without the permission of the monks is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.32"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.33"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.34"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.35"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.35a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2417"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.159"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.36"
msgid ""
"Atirekachāratte atirekasaññī vippavasati, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, "
"nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than six days and he perceives it as more and he is staying "
"apart from it, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.37"
msgid ""
"Atirekachāratte vematiko vippavasati, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ "
"pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than six days, but he is unsure if it is, and he is staying "
"apart from it, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.38"
msgid ""
"Atirekachāratte ūnakasaññī vippavasati, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, "
"nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than six days, but he does not perceives it as more, and he is "
"staying apart from it, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an "
"offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.39"
msgid "Appaccuddhaṭe paccuddhaṭasaññī … pe …"
msgstr ""
"If the determination has not been given up, but he perceives it as given up …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.40"
msgid "avissajjite vissajjitasaññī …"
msgstr ""
"If the robe has not been given away, but he perceives it as given away …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.41"
msgid "anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If the robe has not been lost, but he perceives it as lost …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.42"
msgid "avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If the robe has not been destroyed, but he perceives it as destroyed …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.43"
msgid "adaḍḍhe daḍḍhasaññī …"
msgstr "If the robe has not been burnt, but he perceives it as burnt …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.44"
msgid ""
"avilutte viluttasaññī vippavasati, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ "
"pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the robe has not been stolen, but he perceives it as stolen, and he is "
"staying apart from it, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an "
"offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2418"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.45"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ cīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he uses a robe that should be relinquished without first relinquishing "
"it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.46"
msgid "Ūnakachāratte atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than six days, but he perceives it as more, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.47"
msgid "Ūnakachāratte vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than six days, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.48"
msgid "Ūnakachāratte ūnakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than six days and he perceives it as less, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.48a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2419"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.49"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.50"
msgid "chārattaṃ vippavasati,"
msgstr "if he stays apart from the robe for six days;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.51"
msgid "ūnakachārattaṃ vippavasati,"
msgstr "if he stays apart from the robe for less than six days;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.52"
msgid "chārattaṃ vippavasitvā puna gāmasīmaṃ okkamitvā vasitvā pakkamati,"
msgstr ""
"if, after staying apart from it for six days, he stays overnight within the "
"village boundary and then departs;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.53"
msgid ""
"antochārattaṃ paccuddharati, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, ḍayhati, "
"acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr ""
"if within the six days he gives up the determination, or the robe is given "
"away, lost, destroyed, burnt, stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.54"
msgid "bhikkhusammutiyā,"
msgstr "if he has the permission of the monks;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.55"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.56"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2420"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:pts-cs2.57"
msgid "Sāsaṅkasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr "The ninth rule, the training rule on what is risky, is finished."

